-- London Development Agency to Sell 70-Acre Former Ford Factory
-- B y   N e i l   C a l l a n a n
-- 2012-03-06T15:36:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/london-development-agency-to-sell-70-acre-former-ford-factory.html
The  London Development Agency  is
seeking to sell a 70-acre former  Ford Motor Co. (F)  factory in east
 London , according to a statement from the mayor’s office.  The site is less than 10 miles (16 kilometers) from
London’s Olympic stadium.  London  Mayor  Boris Johnson ’s office
referred questions on the value of the land to Michael Burdus, a
director at broker Drivers Jonas Deloitte. Burdus wasn’t
immediately available for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Neil Callanan in London at 
 ncallanan@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Andrew Blackman  at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net . 